1
00:00:39,933 --> 00:00:41,100
<i> Give me that!</i>

2
00:00:41,233 --> 00:00:43,200
<i>Do you really have to interfere
with my phone calls, too?</i>

3
00:00:43,333 --> 00:00:45,067
<i>I said I'm sorry!
What else do you want?</i>

4
00:00:45,200 --> 00:00:47,833
<i>Stay out of my life!
That's what I want!</i>

5
00:00:47,967 --> 00:00:49,833
<i>Hello, Jessica?
Where's your dad?</i>

6
00:00:49,967 --> 00:00:51,800
<i> Can we meet?</i>

7
00:00:51,933 --> 00:00:54,033
<i> Oh, yes. I've arrived, Alice.</i>

8
00:00:54,167 --> 00:00:56,567
<i> And I'm ready for war.</i>

9
00:00:56,700 --> 00:00:58,467
<i> Thank you for coming.</i>

10
00:00:58,600 --> 00:01:02,000
<i>I hope you can forgive me for
all the wrongs I've done to you.</i>

11
00:01:02,133 --> 00:01:04,100
<i> I came here to help you.</i>

12
00:01:04,233 --> 00:01:07,733
<i>And for Coleen.
Because she's worried for you.</i>

13
00:01:07,900 --> 00:01:09,233
<i>I wish you had brought Coleen
with you.</i>

14
00:01:09,367 --> 00:01:13,100
<i>I don't want Andrea and Jeff
to get mad at my lastborn.</i>

15
00:01:13,233 --> 00:01:15,067
<i>Make her come out,
if you don't want to let me in!</i>

16
00:01:15,200 --> 00:01:17,600
<i>Call her!
Tell your home wrecker boss</i>

17
00:01:17,733 --> 00:01:19,533
<i>that Hazel Capistrano Cruz
is here!</i>

18
00:01:19,667 --> 00:01:20,500
<i> Come with me!</i>

19
00:01:20,633 --> 00:01:21,433
<i>- Follow me!
- What are you doing?</i>

20
00:01:21,567 --> 00:01:23,933
<i>- Who are you?
- I'm Abel's wife.</i>

21
00:01:24,067 --> 00:01:26,667
<i> You need my help.</i>

22
00:01:26,800 --> 00:01:28,967
<i>What made you think
that I need your help?</i>

23
00:01:29,100 --> 00:01:31,600
<i> I can bring Manuel to you.</i>

24
00:01:37,567 --> 00:01:39,433
Hello, Coleen?

25
00:01:39,567 --> 00:01:41,233
- Hi, Jessica!
- Hey!

26
00:01:41,400 --> 00:01:42,967
It's good to hear
from you again.

27
00:01:43,100 --> 00:01:44,233
How are you?

28
00:01:44,367 --> 00:01:45,600
I'm good.

29
00:01:48,900 --> 00:01:50,000
Jessica...

30
00:01:51,033 --> 00:01:53,033
Can I see you and Dad?

31
00:02:02,533 --> 00:02:06,200
All is good, Felma. I've already
driven away the evil spirit.

32
00:02:08,633 --> 00:02:10,467
What did you do
to make her leave?

33
00:02:12,333 --> 00:02:13,233
I threatened her.

34
00:02:13,367 --> 00:02:16,167
I told her I hired a hitman.

35
00:02:17,833 --> 00:02:19,967
And she believed you?

36
00:02:20,100 --> 00:02:21,733
Yes!

37
00:02:21,867 --> 00:02:23,600
So the crazy girl
gets scared too.

38
00:02:23,733 --> 00:02:26,233
All she can do is run her mouth.

39
00:02:30,367 --> 00:02:31,900
Thank you, Paz.

40
00:02:39,400 --> 00:02:40,633
What's wrong with you, Abel?

41
00:02:40,767 --> 00:02:41,833
What?

42
00:02:41,967 --> 00:02:44,200
I don't believe that you don't
know where Manuel is!

43
00:02:44,333 --> 00:02:46,067
- Tell me!
- I really don't know!

44
00:02:46,200 --> 00:02:48,000
What are you saying?

45
00:02:48,167 --> 00:02:49,633
You're unbelievable.

46
00:02:49,767 --> 00:02:52,533
I thought we weren't allowed
to communicate?

47
00:02:52,667 --> 00:02:54,500
Fine, fine!
I'm giving you permission.

48
00:02:54,633 --> 00:02:57,900
Call him. Go!
So I'll know where he is!

49
00:02:58,033 --> 00:02:59,367
Find out where he stays!

50
00:02:59,500 --> 00:03:00,400
What are you planning?

51
00:03:00,533 --> 00:03:01,467
Are you going to pick a fight
with Manuel?

52
00:03:01,600 --> 00:03:02,733
No!

53
00:03:02,867 --> 00:03:03,600
Come on, Abel!

54
00:03:03,733 --> 00:03:05,500
This is for Felma!

55
00:03:05,633 --> 00:03:07,233
No. I don't know.

56
00:03:07,367 --> 00:03:09,700
Don't you want a cuddle time?
Is that it?

57
00:03:09,833 --> 00:03:11,100
Really?

58
00:03:11,233 --> 00:03:12,000
Fine!

59
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:17,067
- What will you do?
- I'm on it!

60
00:03:17,200 --> 00:03:20,367
I knew it! You're lying to me!

61
00:03:20,500 --> 00:03:24,833
Here it is. I wrote it down
during our conversation.

62
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:25,867
You don't want to talk
to Manuel?

63
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:27,167
I do!

64
00:03:27,300 --> 00:03:30,500
Keep it up, and you won't get
any cuddle time later!

65
00:03:30,633 --> 00:03:31,633
Unbelievable.

66
00:03:33,300 --> 00:03:34,533
Do whatever you want!

67
00:03:45,200 --> 00:03:47,967
Hello, Hazel?

68
00:03:48,100 --> 00:03:50,133
Yes. I already know
where Manuel is.

69
00:03:50,267 --> 00:03:53,467
They're staying in an Airbnb.

70
00:03:53,600 --> 00:03:55,167
Yes, I'll send it to you. Okay?

71
00:04:05,433 --> 00:04:07,133
Jessica, what is that?

72
00:04:07,267 --> 00:04:10,400
Dad, we have a visitor.

73
00:04:10,533 --> 00:04:12,667
Who is our visitor?

74
00:04:12,800 --> 00:04:14,733
Dad, it's a surprise.

75
00:04:16,600 --> 00:04:19,700
I'm not a fan of surprises.
Who is our guest?

76
00:04:19,833 --> 00:04:21,667
Ask me later, Dad.

77
00:04:56,733 --> 00:04:58,900
This is it, Dad.

78
00:04:59,033 --> 00:05:00,467
We're finally going to meet.

79
00:05:01,767 --> 00:05:03,600
I'm finally meeting you.

80
00:05:10,967 --> 00:05:12,300
You don't know?

81
00:05:12,433 --> 00:05:14,667
You don't know
where Coleen went?

82
00:05:14,800 --> 00:05:16,433
No, Ma'am.

83
00:05:18,300 --> 00:05:19,367
Jeffrey!

84
00:05:19,500 --> 00:05:21,267
Andrea!

85
00:05:21,400 --> 00:05:22,967
Is Coleen not with you?

86
00:05:23,100 --> 00:05:24,233
No, Mom.

87
00:05:26,067 --> 00:05:28,367
Where could Coleen be?

88
00:05:29,700 --> 00:05:31,367
I've been calling her!

89
00:05:31,500 --> 00:05:32,967
She didn't tell me
where she went!

90
00:05:33,100 --> 00:05:35,533
She's not even answering.
Her cellphone is turned off!

91
00:05:35,700 --> 00:05:38,067
Did you try calling Rona?

92
00:05:39,067 --> 00:05:41,233
Yes, Andrea.

93
00:05:41,367 --> 00:05:42,967
But she also doesn't know.

94
00:05:44,100 --> 00:05:45,900
Oh, no.

95
00:05:46,033 --> 00:05:48,533
Where is that kid?

96
00:05:48,667 --> 00:05:49,933
She doesn't go out at night

97
00:05:50,067 --> 00:05:51,467
without asking
for my permission.

98
00:05:56,300 --> 00:05:58,067
Jeffrey?

99
00:05:58,200 --> 00:05:59,100
Andrea?

100
00:06:00,333 --> 00:06:02,500
Did the three of you
fight again?

101
00:06:15,300 --> 00:06:16,433
Oh, this kid.

102
00:06:17,900 --> 00:06:20,033
Come on, tell me.

103
00:06:20,167 --> 00:06:23,400
Dad, ask me later.
It's a surprise.

104
00:06:42,433 --> 00:06:43,700
Coleen.

105
00:06:45,433 --> 00:06:46,567
Jessica.

106
00:07:04,267 --> 00:07:05,300
Dad?

107
00:07:11,167 --> 00:07:12,367
Coleen?

108
00:07:15,500 --> 00:07:16,367
Dad.

109
00:07:20,900 --> 00:07:22,333
Dad.

110
00:07:22,467 --> 00:07:24,133
Dad!

111
00:07:53,867 --> 00:07:55,233
Dad.

112
00:07:58,400 --> 00:08:00,567
I've done you so much wrong.

113
00:08:01,567 --> 00:08:04,200
Dear, I hope you can forgive me.

114
00:08:06,667 --> 00:08:08,833
Please forgive me.

115
00:08:08,967 --> 00:08:11,200
Dad!

116
00:08:24,233 --> 00:08:25,533
Jessica.

117
00:08:36,000 --> 00:08:37,267
Dad.

118
00:08:47,500 --> 00:08:49,133
Answer me!

119
00:08:49,267 --> 00:08:52,600
Did the three of you
fight again? Did you?

120
00:08:54,400 --> 00:08:56,300
Andrea and Coleen
had an argument,

121
00:08:56,467 --> 00:08:57,800
but it was a long time ago.

122
00:08:57,933 --> 00:08:59,733
It's Coleen's fault.

123
00:08:59,867 --> 00:09:03,433
For sure, she did something,
and she's keeping it from us.

124
00:09:03,567 --> 00:09:04,633
Andrea!

125
00:09:04,767 --> 00:09:07,667
We are thinking
the same thing, Jeff.

126
00:09:07,800 --> 00:09:11,533
The person she wants to see
is here in the Philippines.

127
00:09:11,667 --> 00:09:13,667
Where else would she go?

128
00:09:19,900 --> 00:09:21,567
Hello?

129
00:09:21,700 --> 00:09:23,967
Are you sure
this is the address?

130
00:09:24,100 --> 00:09:27,133
I'm warning you! You better not
be lying, or you'll pay for it!

131
00:09:32,667 --> 00:09:33,867
Yes, Ma'am.

132
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:35,167
Thank you.

133
00:09:36,867 --> 00:09:38,333
Hold on, Ma'am.

134
00:09:38,467 --> 00:09:39,567
Where are you heading?

135
00:09:44,633 --> 00:09:45,567
Fourth floor.

136
00:09:45,700 --> 00:09:46,533
406.

137
00:09:46,667 --> 00:09:48,600
406. May I know your name?

138
00:09:48,733 --> 00:09:50,067
- Hazel.
- Hazel.

139
00:09:50,200 --> 00:09:52,033
Hazel Cruz.

140
00:09:52,167 --> 00:09:52,967
Dad.

141
00:09:54,167 --> 00:09:57,500
I've forgiven you
a long time ago.

142
00:09:57,633 --> 00:10:00,367
Thank you so much, Coleen.

143
00:10:00,500 --> 00:10:01,867
Thank you.

144
00:10:02,800 --> 00:10:04,000
Jessica...

145
00:10:05,300 --> 00:10:07,700
I'm glad to meet you in person.

146
00:10:07,833 --> 00:10:09,367
Same here, Coleen.

147
00:10:10,633 --> 00:10:12,933
Ma'am, you're not
on the visitor's list.

148
00:10:13,067 --> 00:10:15,067
I'll call the occupant first.

149
00:10:22,133 --> 00:10:23,367
Who's calling?

150
00:10:29,333 --> 00:10:30,233
Hello?

151
00:10:30,367 --> 00:10:31,233
<i> Hello, Ma'am?</i>

152
00:10:31,367 --> 00:10:32,833
Miss Hazel is here.

153
00:10:36,067 --> 00:10:37,200
What?

154
00:10:37,333 --> 00:10:39,767
Sir, please.
Don't let her go upstairs.

155
00:10:42,800 --> 00:10:44,567
They told me
not to let you go upstairs.

156
00:10:44,700 --> 00:10:46,100
What?

157
00:10:46,233 --> 00:10:49,500
Dad, Mom is here.

158
00:10:49,633 --> 00:10:50,600
She's here in the Philippines?

159
00:10:51,800 --> 00:10:53,633
How could she find us?

160
00:10:53,767 --> 00:10:55,267
That can't be!

161
00:10:55,400 --> 00:10:56,433
Ma'am!

162
00:10:56,567 --> 00:10:58,833
You can't get inside!

163
00:10:58,967 --> 00:11:00,900
- No!
- Ma'am, you can't go upstairs!

164
00:11:01,033 --> 00:11:03,433
- What are you blabbering about?
- You can't go upstairs!

165
00:11:03,567 --> 00:11:05,867
- No!
- It's the occupant's order!

166
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:07,767
Let go of me!

167
00:11:15,100 --> 00:11:16,033
Roving!

168
00:11:16,167 --> 00:11:18,033
A woman is going
to the fourth floor!

169
00:11:18,167 --> 00:11:21,100
Stop her at the fire exit!

170
00:11:21,233 --> 00:11:22,100
Dad!

171
00:11:22,233 --> 00:11:24,767
Dad! Mom is on her way here.

172
00:11:24,900 --> 00:11:28,533
She must not get to us, Coleen.
She'll bring us back to Canada!

173
00:11:28,667 --> 00:11:30,000
Where would we go?

174
00:11:30,133 --> 00:11:32,400
To Abel.

175
00:11:32,533 --> 00:11:33,800
Dad, we can't do that!

176
00:11:33,933 --> 00:11:36,067
Godmother Paz will tell Mom!

177
00:11:37,433 --> 00:11:38,633
Wait.

178
00:11:38,767 --> 00:11:40,167
I have an idea.

179
00:11:40,300 --> 00:11:41,633
Leave it to me.

180
00:11:45,633 --> 00:11:47,067
Manuel.

181
00:11:55,633 --> 00:11:56,800
Manuel!

182
00:12:01,300 --> 00:12:03,033
Let's go, Dad.

183
00:12:03,167 --> 00:12:04,033
Dad!

184
00:12:04,167 --> 00:12:05,700
Dad, our ride is just
two minutes away.

185
00:12:05,833 --> 00:12:08,000
Where are we going?

186
00:12:08,133 --> 00:12:10,533
I heard the guard
that Mom used the stairs.

187
00:12:16,900 --> 00:12:18,767
Go, go, go! Dad!

188
00:12:20,567 --> 00:12:21,900
Coleen.

189
00:12:22,033 --> 00:12:22,933
Jessica.

190
00:12:23,067 --> 00:12:24,600
Let's go!

191
00:12:24,733 --> 00:12:29,000
Wait! I left my bag! Our
passports and money are there.

192
00:12:29,133 --> 00:12:29,967
- What?
- Wait! Hold on, Coleen!

193
00:12:30,100 --> 00:12:31,300
Hurry!

194
00:12:31,433 --> 00:12:32,400
Jessica!

195
00:12:33,467 --> 00:12:34,733
How dare you run away from me!

196
00:12:34,867 --> 00:12:36,233
- Come here!
- Jessica!

197
00:12:36,367 --> 00:12:39,133
How dare you involve our child,
Manuel!

198
00:12:39,267 --> 00:12:40,400
Come here!

199
00:12:40,533 --> 00:12:41,733
Hazel!

200
00:12:41,867 --> 00:12:43,967
Jessica!

201
00:12:45,467 --> 00:12:46,533
Hey!

202
00:12:46,667 --> 00:12:48,100
Hey!

203
00:13:00,200 --> 00:13:01,467
How dare you!

204
00:13:07,667 --> 00:13:08,300
Roving!

205
00:13:08,433 --> 00:13:09,900
Status?

206
00:13:10,033 --> 00:13:11,533
Are you already
on the fourth floor?

207
00:13:19,833 --> 00:13:21,000
Ma'am! Sir!

208
00:13:21,167 --> 00:13:22,233
What happened?

209
00:13:28,933 --> 00:13:29,867
- Roving!
- Manuel!

210
00:13:30,000 --> 00:13:32,200
Jessica!
Do you think you can escape me?

211
00:13:32,333 --> 00:13:33,233
- Ma'am!
- Manuel! Jessica!

212
00:13:33,367 --> 00:13:35,633
What happened, Ma'am?

213
00:13:37,400 --> 00:13:40,633
- Mom is here, Coleen! Go!
- I'll get on the other side!

214
00:13:40,767 --> 00:13:42,467
- Jessica!
- Go!

215
00:13:42,600 --> 00:13:44,433
- Manuel!
- Go!

216
00:13:44,567 --> 00:13:46,500
You can't run away from me!

217
00:13:46,633 --> 00:13:48,133
Jessica!

218
00:14:02,033 --> 00:14:03,333
They escaped me!

219
00:14:03,467 --> 00:14:06,167
Is it my fault
that you're dumb?

220
00:14:06,300 --> 00:14:07,533
Shut up!

221
00:14:08,567 --> 00:14:10,433
I know they're with Felma.

222
00:14:10,567 --> 00:14:12,067
They have nowhere else to go.

223
00:14:12,200 --> 00:14:14,300
So, give me Felma's address.

224
00:14:14,433 --> 00:14:17,800
Am I crazy?
Why would I give it to you?

225
00:14:17,933 --> 00:14:22,000
You're the only one
obsessed with your husband!

226
00:14:22,133 --> 00:14:24,100
Felma is nothing like you!

227
00:14:24,233 --> 00:14:26,600
I thought you would help me?

228
00:14:26,733 --> 00:14:30,100
I will never give you
my best friend's home address.

229
00:14:30,267 --> 00:14:34,300
So, shut up
and stop disturbing me!

230
00:14:34,433 --> 00:14:35,967
You're ruining the vibes!

231
00:14:39,233 --> 00:14:40,700
Darling...

232
00:14:40,833 --> 00:14:42,200
Who were you fighting with?

233
00:14:42,333 --> 00:14:46,100
How dare you!

234
00:14:46,233 --> 00:14:48,300
Don't you dare hang up on me.

235
00:14:49,533 --> 00:14:51,200
Darling...

236
00:14:51,333 --> 00:14:52,867
It's cuddle time!

237
00:14:56,933 --> 00:14:59,733
Ling.

238
00:14:59,867 --> 00:15:02,833
Ling, Ling, Ling!

239
00:15:03,000 --> 00:15:05,133
Ling, not there.
That tickles me.

240
00:15:05,267 --> 00:15:06,733
I know.

241
00:15:06,867 --> 00:15:09,933
That's why I'm doing it.
Because you like it, right?

242
00:15:11,633 --> 00:15:13,467
- There, there, there!
- Oh, Ling!

243
00:15:13,600 --> 00:15:15,433
Ling, Ling, Ling!

244
00:15:15,567 --> 00:15:16,767
Yuck!

245
00:15:16,900 --> 00:15:18,100
Yuck!

246
00:15:19,933 --> 00:15:21,200
Hello, Didang?

247
00:15:21,333 --> 00:15:22,967
Can you please open the gate?

248
00:15:23,100 --> 00:15:25,300
Is anyone home?

249
00:15:25,433 --> 00:15:27,200
<i> Coleen, I'm glad you're home.</i>

250
00:15:27,333 --> 00:15:29,200
Where did you go?

251
00:15:29,333 --> 00:15:30,433
Are you there?

252
00:15:30,567 --> 00:15:31,633
Didang!

253
00:15:31,767 --> 00:15:33,000
Wait, I'm coming.

254
00:15:34,333 --> 00:15:35,767
I'm coming, I'm coming.

255
00:15:35,933 --> 00:15:36,867
Wait a minute.

256
00:15:37,800 --> 00:15:39,000
Come here.

257
00:15:44,467 --> 00:15:45,667
Coleen?

258
00:15:51,100 --> 00:15:53,467
Oh, my!

259
00:15:53,600 --> 00:15:55,333
Sir Manuel, is that you?

260
00:15:56,733 --> 00:15:58,100
I know.

261
00:15:59,467 --> 00:16:02,100
Didang, I'll explain it later.

262
00:16:02,233 --> 00:16:04,867
Help me get them in
through the back.

263
00:16:05,000 --> 00:16:05,967
Come on! Let's go!

264
00:16:06,100 --> 00:16:07,633
Come on, hurry up!

265
00:16:09,567 --> 00:16:11,833
- That's what we think.
- Oh, my! It's your brother.

266
00:16:11,967 --> 00:16:14,100
Coleen went to see her dad.

267
00:16:14,233 --> 00:16:15,367
I don't understand her.

268
00:16:15,500 --> 00:16:16,767
She's so stubborn.

269
00:16:17,767 --> 00:16:20,067
- Go!
- She hasn't gone home yet.

270
00:16:26,033 --> 00:16:27,367
Dad, be careful.

271
00:16:36,567 --> 00:16:37,600
So, that's the reason
why you were not telling us

272
00:16:37,733 --> 00:16:40,200
where we were going.
This is where you'd bring us.

273
00:16:40,333 --> 00:16:41,800
Dad, don't worry.

274
00:16:41,967 --> 00:16:43,567
No one will know.

275
00:16:44,567 --> 00:16:46,100
Okay, go to bed now.

276
00:16:47,133 --> 00:16:48,233
Okay, bye.

277
00:16:50,733 --> 00:16:51,633
Didang?

278
00:16:56,567 --> 00:16:58,933
Who were you talking to?
Were you talking to someone?

279
00:16:59,067 --> 00:17:00,533
No, Jeff.

280
00:17:00,667 --> 00:17:04,067
I just checked.
Since I thought I heard a knock.

281
00:17:04,200 --> 00:17:05,300
I just took a quick look.

282
00:17:05,433 --> 00:17:06,533
Yes.

283
00:17:06,667 --> 00:17:08,533
Is Coleen home?

284
00:17:08,667 --> 00:17:10,767
Not yet.

285
00:17:10,900 --> 00:17:13,167
But she's probably
in the clubhouse.

286
00:17:13,300 --> 00:17:15,600
Don't worry. I'll pick her up.

287
00:17:15,767 --> 00:17:18,067
So she'll get home.

288
00:17:18,200 --> 00:17:19,300
Wait.

289
00:17:23,867 --> 00:17:25,567
Here's Coleen!

290
00:17:25,700 --> 00:17:26,900
Where have you been?

291
00:17:27,800 --> 00:17:30,033
We were all worried for you!

292
00:17:30,167 --> 00:17:32,933
Jeff, save that for tomorrow.

293
00:17:33,067 --> 00:17:33,967
I'm tired.

294
00:17:35,900 --> 00:17:37,967
Why are you being disrespectful?

295
00:17:38,100 --> 00:17:39,433
Jeff!

296
00:17:39,567 --> 00:17:41,300
I said I'm tired!

297
00:17:45,467 --> 00:17:46,733
Coleen!

298
00:17:46,867 --> 00:17:48,167
Coleen, let's talk...

299
00:17:48,300 --> 00:17:49,367
Coleen!

300
00:17:53,333 --> 00:17:54,333
Sir Manuel?

301
00:17:54,467 --> 00:17:55,567
Sir Manuel?

302
00:17:55,700 --> 00:17:57,267
Come on! Hurry!

303
00:17:57,400 --> 00:17:58,467
Hurry!

304
00:17:58,600 --> 00:18:00,100
Let's go inside.

305
00:18:09,800 --> 00:18:15,567
The CR is outside,
in the dirty kitchen.

306
00:18:15,967 --> 00:18:19,033
If you're going to use it,
just be cautious.

307
00:18:19,167 --> 00:18:21,900
Peek first
in case someone's there.

308
00:18:22,067 --> 00:18:25,367
And please excuse the state
of this storage room.

309
00:18:25,500 --> 00:18:29,133
Aside from being messy,
it's also full of dust.

310
00:18:29,267 --> 00:18:31,600
No.

311
00:18:31,733 --> 00:18:33,633
This is good enough.

312
00:18:34,767 --> 00:18:35,767
Thank you, Didang.

313
00:18:35,900 --> 00:18:37,600
You ended up involved.

314
00:18:37,733 --> 00:18:41,733
Don't worry about that, Sir.
I can't say no to Coleen anyway.

315
00:18:43,433 --> 00:18:46,433
Wait. I'll get you some food.

316
00:18:46,567 --> 00:18:51,800
And I'll bring an electric fan
before I start fixing this.

317
00:18:51,933 --> 00:18:52,567
- Excuse me.
- Wait.

318
00:18:52,700 --> 00:18:54,400
Where could Coleen be?

319
00:18:54,533 --> 00:18:56,367
She might get an earful
from her mom.

320
00:18:56,533 --> 00:19:01,833
Probably not if she manages
to get away with what she did.

321
00:19:01,967 --> 00:19:04,167
Leaving without
asking permission.

322
00:19:04,300 --> 00:19:08,100
But with the other two,
Jeff and Andrea, oh, no,

323
00:19:08,233 --> 00:19:09,600
that's not going to end well
for her.

324
00:19:09,733 --> 00:19:10,633
You know what?

325
00:19:10,767 --> 00:19:14,200
They feel that Coleen
went to meet with you.

326
00:19:16,333 --> 00:19:17,800
I'll leave you for now.

327
00:19:17,933 --> 00:19:18,867
Thank you, Didang.

328
00:19:19,000 --> 00:19:20,800
- Thank you.
- Okay.

329
00:19:36,933 --> 00:19:38,833
You're really not listening!

330
00:19:38,967 --> 00:19:40,700
You're not just disrespecting
Andrea and I!

331
00:19:40,833 --> 00:19:42,667
Even Mom.
Where did you go?

332
00:19:42,800 --> 00:19:45,100
Why did you even ask?
She went to see her father!

333
00:19:45,233 --> 00:19:47,433
Yes, I went to see Dad.

334
00:19:47,567 --> 00:19:48,767
You really are so stubborn!

335
00:19:48,900 --> 00:19:50,067
You're so disrespectful!

336
00:19:50,200 --> 00:19:51,567
Andrea!

337
00:19:55,167 --> 00:19:56,800
Haven't we talked already?

338
00:19:56,933 --> 00:19:58,867
Your lastborn is really rude!

339
00:19:59,000 --> 00:20:02,300
Look, she's not listening
to you! She doesn't respect you!

340
00:20:02,467 --> 00:20:07,600
Sorry if meeting with Dad
offends you and Jeff!

341
00:20:07,733 --> 00:20:10,600
Mom, I'm sorry
for disrespecting you.

342
00:20:13,333 --> 00:20:15,067
But I'm okay now.

343
00:20:16,933 --> 00:20:19,067
I've finally met my dad.

344
00:20:20,333 --> 00:20:22,300
I've finally talked to him,

345
00:20:22,433 --> 00:20:23,800
and hugged him.

346
00:20:25,800 --> 00:20:27,667
My dream has finally come true.

347
00:20:32,233 --> 00:20:33,567
So, it's over.

348
00:20:34,733 --> 00:20:36,567
I won't see him anymore.

349
00:20:38,133 --> 00:20:40,600
You really think
we would still believe you?

350
00:20:40,733 --> 00:20:41,700
No!

351
00:20:42,900 --> 00:20:46,800
Because you will never believe
whatever I say, right?

352
00:20:46,933 --> 00:20:51,733
If that's the case,
I might as well go to him.

353
00:20:51,867 --> 00:20:54,200
Never do that, Coleen!

354
00:20:54,333 --> 00:20:55,300
I dare you!

355
00:21:04,367 --> 00:21:05,967
I didn't teach you...

356
00:21:06,100 --> 00:21:08,067
to talk back to your siblings!

357
00:21:09,367 --> 00:21:10,700
We've already talked,
haven't we?

358
00:21:11,700 --> 00:21:14,067
That you would never
call your dad again!

359
00:21:14,200 --> 00:21:15,667
Because you knew exactly
how this would turn out!

360
00:21:15,800 --> 00:21:16,933
Trouble!

361
00:21:18,167 --> 00:21:20,167
You should have just said no,

362
00:21:20,300 --> 00:21:22,200
if you were planning to disobey
me anyway!

363
00:21:23,200 --> 00:21:24,833
You're insulting me.

364
00:21:25,867 --> 00:21:27,733
You're hurting my feelings!

365
00:21:30,667 --> 00:21:31,700
Mom!

366
00:21:33,467 --> 00:21:35,200
I'm sorry.

367
00:21:35,333 --> 00:21:38,300
It wasn't my intention
to hurt you.

368
00:22:06,667 --> 00:22:07,733
Where's Coleen?

369
00:22:11,533 --> 00:22:14,333
According to Didang,
she's not feeling well.

370
00:22:19,067 --> 00:22:20,733
Is she feeling sick,
or is she just upset?

371
00:22:20,867 --> 00:22:22,833
Wow, so she's
the one acting hurt now?

372
00:22:22,967 --> 00:22:25,700
It feels strange having
breakfast without Coleen.

373
00:22:25,833 --> 00:22:27,500
I'll pick her up.

374
00:22:27,633 --> 00:22:29,833
Here we go again, Jeff.

375
00:22:29,967 --> 00:22:31,333
You've been coddling
her too much.

376
00:22:31,467 --> 00:22:33,633
That's why she's starting
to get spoiled.

377
00:22:33,767 --> 00:22:36,000
Yes, Coleen made a mistake.

378
00:22:36,133 --> 00:22:37,900
But don't you feel
sorry for her?

379
00:22:38,033 --> 00:22:39,333
We're all mad at her.

380
00:22:41,633 --> 00:22:42,733
Leave her be.

381
00:22:42,867 --> 00:22:44,300
Leave her be for now, Jeff.

382
00:22:44,433 --> 00:22:46,267
She'll go downstairs
once she gets hungry.

383
00:22:46,400 --> 00:22:50,833
And let me talk to her.

384
00:22:51,000 --> 00:22:52,133
Okay.

385
00:22:56,900 --> 00:22:58,367
Andrea.

386
00:23:06,800 --> 00:23:09,167
Out of all the places
we could've hidden,

387
00:23:09,300 --> 00:23:11,933
it had to be Felma's house?

388
00:23:12,067 --> 00:23:13,933
It's embarrassing.

389
00:23:14,067 --> 00:23:17,600
What happened last night
was unexpected.

390
00:23:17,733 --> 00:23:19,967
I'm worried about
your sister Coleen.

391
00:23:21,600 --> 00:23:24,133
We must leave this place
as soon as possible.

392
00:23:24,267 --> 00:23:26,833
We'll look for another Airbnb.

393
00:23:26,967 --> 00:23:29,900
Dear, can we find an apartment
instead?

394
00:23:30,033 --> 00:23:32,467
Go and search online.

395
00:23:32,600 --> 00:23:34,367
Okay.

396
00:23:34,500 --> 00:23:37,433
Dad, we need to drop
by the Airbnb first.

397
00:23:37,567 --> 00:23:40,833
Because we need to get
our stuff and money.

398
00:23:40,967 --> 00:23:42,867
Okay.

399
00:23:43,000 --> 00:23:45,567
But what if your mom comes back
there?

400
00:23:45,700 --> 00:23:47,667
I'll call the owner first
to check.

401
00:23:47,800 --> 00:23:50,167
They live in the same building.

402
00:23:57,033 --> 00:23:58,300
- Coleen.
- Jessica.

403
00:24:02,900 --> 00:24:08,167
Dad, Jessica, sorry I wasn't
able to return last night.

404
00:24:08,300 --> 00:24:10,833
I'm just being careful.

405
00:24:10,967 --> 00:24:13,467
Jessica, here are
some of my clothes.

406
00:24:15,767 --> 00:24:17,333
It will fit you.

407
00:24:17,467 --> 00:24:18,500
Thank you.

408
00:24:18,633 --> 00:24:20,300
And you, Dad.

409
00:24:20,433 --> 00:24:22,500
Here are Jeff's old clothes.

410
00:24:22,633 --> 00:24:24,533
You can get clothes here.

411
00:24:24,667 --> 00:24:25,767
Thank you.

412
00:24:30,167 --> 00:24:32,900
Why?

413
00:24:33,033 --> 00:24:35,767
Didang came earlier.

414
00:24:35,900 --> 00:24:37,733
I heard that you got scolded
last night.

415
00:24:39,500 --> 00:24:43,933
Dear, seeing me
is already a big issue.

416
00:24:44,067 --> 00:24:46,733
What if they find out
that we're here?

417
00:24:46,867 --> 00:24:48,667
We need to get out of here
quickly.

418
00:24:48,800 --> 00:24:50,400
What?

419
00:24:50,533 --> 00:24:53,167
Dad, don't go.

420
00:24:53,300 --> 00:24:55,667
I want to spend more time
with you and Jessica.

421
00:24:55,800 --> 00:24:57,400
I'm sorry, Coleen,

422
00:24:57,533 --> 00:24:59,300
but I agree with Dad.

423
00:24:59,433 --> 00:25:02,133
We really want to spend
as much time with you.

424
00:25:02,300 --> 00:25:04,433
But we don't want to risk
your relationship

425
00:25:04,567 --> 00:25:06,000
with your family.

426
00:25:13,700 --> 00:25:14,433
Hello, Bro?

427
00:25:14,567 --> 00:25:15,767
Hello, Manuel! Where are you?

428
00:25:15,900 --> 00:25:18,133
- That's enough! Stop it, Paz!
- No! I won't stop!

429
00:25:18,267 --> 00:25:20,767
I want to teach
your best friend a lesson!

430
00:25:20,900 --> 00:25:24,900
Did you know that this scumbag
is using his daughter with Hazel

431
00:25:25,033 --> 00:25:28,200
<i>so he could ask for help
from Felma?</i>

432
00:25:28,333 --> 00:25:30,500
<i> Isn't that conning?</i>

433
00:25:30,633 --> 00:25:31,633
<i> Do you understand me?</i>

434
00:25:31,767 --> 00:25:32,867
<i> You're so shameless!</i>

435
00:25:33,000 --> 00:25:35,467
This is Stephanie Lim,
from Value More.

436
00:25:35,633 --> 00:25:37,133
At your service, yes.

437
00:25:37,267 --> 00:25:39,267
We would like to send
a VIP invitation

438
00:25:39,400 --> 00:25:40,867
for Miss Felma Ruiz.

439
00:25:41,000 --> 00:25:43,933
And for Miss Paz Antonio.

440
00:25:44,067 --> 00:25:45,167
Get your pen and paper.

441
00:25:45,300 --> 00:25:47,967
I'll dictate to you
our addresses.

442
00:25:48,100 --> 00:25:49,467
Felma!

443
00:25:49,600 --> 00:25:51,367
Felma slut!

444
00:25:51,500 --> 00:25:52,767
Dad!

445
00:25:52,900 --> 00:25:54,433
Your wife is outside!

446
00:25:54,567 --> 00:25:55,867
- What?
- My mom?

447
00:25:56,000 --> 00:25:57,533
You need to hide!

448
00:25:57,667 --> 00:25:59,100
No, I'll confront Hazel.

449
00:25:59,233 --> 00:26:00,567
Felma needs help.

450
00:26:00,700 --> 00:26:02,933
Get Manuel and Jessica out here!

451
00:26:03,067 --> 00:26:04,633
How did you get in here?
